metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #213
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Shoji #107
metadata.description:
A shoji is a traditional Japanese screen, consisting of translucent sheets on a lattice frame. 

This work used two shoji-inspired lattices, overlayed so they form a composite pattern. The geometry of each lattice is then manipulated to produce organic curves and playful interactions between the layers. 

This is an animated loop, but can be paused as required.

:: Shortcut keys ::
Space - pause/play the animation
S - save a PNG image at 4000 x 4000 px

- - - - - 

Made with code and love by AutoEclectus.
